review:
-Além de limitar a ter 1 só personagem, limita também o skill cap até no máximo 60. Pra um jogo free isso já assusta;
-Os gráficos não são tão legais, demora nos loadings e otimização também não agradou;
-Tutorial muito simples para complexidade do jogo, mostrando apenas o básico do básico, e te vira ao Deus dará;

Continuei jogando, e de tão parado que o jogo é, desinstalei e fui procurar outro MMORPG.

+ Great, original ideas; great setting; beautiful enviroment; original take on magic, fighting and fantasy-based genre; limitless gameplay; fun and challenging combat; unique and intriguing skilltrees; custom player built castles/walls/buildings/bridges/etc; often great, sympathetic, helpful community; guild-based world wars; lore written and created by players; self-established story goodguy/badguy through guild relations.

- Often buggy; small developer team so slow (but steady) progress; some controversy about corrupt devs (but believe what you want to believe); mostly meta-based combat (most effective weapons/tactics/builds); little to no tutorial; not quite complete (bugs and glitches); sometimes nasty, unhelpful community (griefing/verbal abuse) also towards new players; p2win; need to play multiple hours at a time to get anything done; practically unplayable with lower fps; 

Tried to even out pro's and cons, so it's up to you wether you play it. I have played it for a while and really liked it, but beware, if you are easily addicted to games, like me, Mortal Online will suck you in and never let you go. Definitely not for everyone. Enjoy!

Bug no login, muito tempo para conseguir entrar;
Gráfico médio;
Complicado, díficil de fazer coisas básicas.

Can't even leave the starting zone without getting killed by veteran players... Don't waste your time. 1/10 Also combat is a joke. Absolutely awful game, right down to its 2005 graphics. 


